tab- tabs banane ke liye simply hume 3 chiz chahiye hoti hai
        TabBar                -     tab ui screen ke liye hota hai
        TabBarView            -     us tab me kya view dikhna chahiye hota hai
        DefaultTabController  -     ye dono chiz ko control karta hai ki kis tab me kaon sa view dikhna chahiye



Note- simply tab banane ke liye hum DefaultTabController iske andar length dete hai ki kitne tabs hai apne pass. aur iske child me hum scaffold banate hai
scaffold ke andar hum appbar, title aur bottom property ka use karte hai hum bottom ke andar tabBar banayenge tabs aur ye jo tabs hai wo ek list leta hai apne andar jiske andar hum Tabs ka use karke tab ka ui likhte hai ki kaisa dikhega
aur scaffold ke body me hum tabbarview ko call karenge jo ki children leta hai ye bhi ek list hai aur isme hum view likhte hai. jo hum pahla widget likhenge wo pahle screen ke liye hoga aur jo hum dusra widget likhenge wo dusre screen ke liye hoga aur jo hum teesra widget likhenge wo 3rd screen ke liye hoga


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const MaterialApp(
      home: MyTabBarScreen(),
      debugShowCheckedModeBanner: false,
    );
  }
}

class MyTabBarScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyTabBarScreen({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return DefaultTabController(
      length: 3, // number of tabs
      child: Scaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(
          title: const Text('Simple TabBar Example'),
          bottom: const TabBar(
            tabs: [
              Tab(text: "Home"),
              Tab(text: "Profile"),
              Tab(text: "Settings"),
            ],
          ),
        ),
        body: const TabBarView(
          children: [
            Center(child: Text("Home Screen")),
            Center(child: Text("Profile Screen")),
            Center(child: Text("Settings Screen")),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
